{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, it has become common for GenAI foundation model developers to scrape data from a wider range of uncurated sources.",
    "Dataset publishers only provide a list of URLs to constitute the dataset, and the domains serving those URLs can expire or be purchased, and the resources can be replaced by an attacker.",
    "As with PredAI models (discussed in Section 2.1), this could lead to TARGETED POISONING ATTACKS, BACKDOOR POISONING ATTACKS, and MODEL POISONING.",
    "A simple mitigation is for datasets to list both the URL and a cryptographic hash of the content that can be verifed by the downloader.",
    "However, this technique may not scale up well for some of the large distributed datasets on the Internet -see Section 4.1 for further information."
  ]
}